The article discusses the President's plan for economic growth and deficit reduction. The plan aims to create conditions for businesses to hire and provide economic security for middle-class families. It follows a balanced approach, asking everyone to do their part and pay their fair share. The plan includes tax cuts for businesses, investments in infrastructure and education, job opportunities for those looking for work, and tax relief for American workers and families. It also outlines how the plan will be paid for, including cuts to discretionary spending, reforms to mandatory programs, tax reform, and health savings. The plan aims to reduce deficits and the national debt, while strengthening Medicare and Medicaid through reducing wasteful spending and erroneous payments. The President also calls for comprehensive tax reform, including lower tax rates, reduction of loopholes, and adherence to the "Buffett Rule" that the wealthy should not pay a smaller share of their income in taxes than middle-class families.